\pard\s9 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:0:0}{\*\cxs PA-R/PA-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}(Proceedings commenced at 10:00 a.m.)\line

\pard\s5 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:3:0}{\*\cxs SREUD/SREUD}\cxsgdelsteno0}THE VIDEOGRAPHER: {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:5:0}{\*\cxs W-R/W-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}We are on the record. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:9:0}{\*\cxs THA/THA}\cxsgdelsteno0}The time is 10:00 a.m. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:14:0}{\*\cxs TH-S/TH-S}\cxsgdelsteno0}This is the videotaped deposition of Earl Ray Thibodaux.\line

\pard\s5 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:22:0}{\*\cxs -T/-T}\cxsgdelsteno0}THE COURT REPORTER: {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:24:0}{\*\cxs PW-R/PW-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}Mr. Thibodaux, do you solemnly swear that the testimony you are about to give will be the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth, so help you God?\line

\pard\s5 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:36:0}{\*\cxs -T/-T}\cxsgdelsteno0}THE WITNESS: {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:38:0}{\*\cxs EUPB/EUPB}\cxsgdelsteno0}I do.\line

\pard\s7 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:42:0}{\*\cxs PWA/PWA}\cxsgdelsteno0}BY MR. HOBBY:\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:45:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:46:0}{\*\cxs PHAEUP/PHAEUP}\cxsgdelsteno0}Please state your name for the record.\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:52:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:53:0}{\*\cxs EARL/EARL}\cxsgdelsteno0}Earl Ray Thibodaux.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:0:59:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:0:0}{\*\cxs WHEUR/WHEUR}\cxsgdelsteno0}Where are you currently employed?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:8:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:9:0}{\*\cxs EUP/EUP}\cxsgdelsteno0}I am a senior petroleum engineer with Lone Star Reservoir Consulting out of Midland, Texas.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:20:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:21:0}{\*\cxs HRO/HRO}\cxsgdelsteno0}How long have you been in the petroleum engineering field?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:29:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:30:0}{\*\cxs TKPW/TKPW}\cxsgdelsteno0}Going on 35 years now. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:35:0}{\*\cxs STA/STA}\cxsgdelsteno0}Started right out of Texas A&M back in 1991.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:44:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:45:0}{\*\cxs A-R/A-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}Are you familiar with seismic interpretation methods used in reservoir analysis?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:55:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:1:56:0}{\*\cxs AOEU/AOEU}\cxsgdelsteno0}Oh yes, sir. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:0:0}{\*\cxs THA/THA}\cxsgdelsteno0}That has been the core of my work for the last 20 years. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:6:0}{\*\cxs W-R/W-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}We use seismic amplitude analysis to identify hydrocarbon-bearing formations.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:18:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:19:0}{\*\cxs KA/KA}\cxsgdelsteno0}Can you explain what you observed in the seismic data for the Yellowrock formation?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:30:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:31:0}{\*\cxs AOEU/AOEU}\cxsgdelsteno0}Yes, sir. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:33:0}{\*\cxs SO/SO}\cxsgdelsteno0}So when we ran the 3D seismic survey over that area, we identified what we call a {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:44:0}{\*\cxs PWRAT/PWRAT}\cxsgdelsteno0}Brat Spot {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:47:0}{\*\cxs EUPB/EUPB}\cxsgdelsteno0}in the amplitude data. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:2:52:0}{\*\cxs THA/THA}\cxsgdelsteno0}That high-amplitude anomaly right there told us there was gas-charged sand at that depth.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:5:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:6:0}{\*\cxs WHA/WHA}\cxsgdelsteno0}What does that Brat Spot indicate specifically?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:14:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:15:0}{\*\cxs WEUL/WEUL}\cxsgdelsteno0}Well, in seismic interpretation, a high-amplitude anomaly like that -- {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:23:0}{\*\cxs EUPBT/EUPBT}\cxsgdelsteno0}and that is industry standard terminology -- {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:29:0}{\*\cxs EUT/EUT}\cxsgdelsteno0}it tells us that the acoustic impedance contrast between the reservoir rock and the overlying shale is very strong. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:42:0}{\*\cxs THA/THA}\cxsgdelsteno0}That is a direct hydrocarbon indicator.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:53:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:54:0}{\*\cxs A-R/A-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}Are you saying that the Brat Spot is what led to the recommendation to drill at that location?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:5:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:3:59:0}{\*\cxs THA/THA}\cxsgdelsteno0}That is correct. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:8:0}{\*\cxs W-T/W-T}\cxsgdelsteno0}Without that anomaly in the seismic, we would not have had the confidence to recommend that well location.\line

\pard\s5 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:19:0}{\*\cxs PHAEUS/PHAEUS}\cxsgdelsteno0}MS. CURTIS: {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:21:0}{\*\cxs SKWR-PB/SKWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Objection. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:23:0}{\*\cxs HREUBG/HREUBG}\cxsgdelsteno0}Leading.\line

\pard\s5 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:26:0}{\*\cxs PHREU/PHREU}\cxsgdelsteno0}MR. HOBBY: {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:27:0}{\*\cxs EUPBL/EUPBL}\cxsgdelsteno0}I'll rephrase.\line

\pard\s1 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:30:0}{\*\cxs KWR-PB/KWR-PB}\cxsgdelsteno0}Q. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:31:0}{\*\cxs WHAT/WHAT}\cxsgdelsteno0}What was the basis for the well location recommendation in your report?\line

\pard\s3 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:40:0}{\*\cxs A/A}\cxsgdelsteno0}A. {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:41:0}{\*\cxs -T/-T}\cxsgdelsteno0}The primary basis was the seismic amplitude anomaly -- {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:47:0}{\*\cxs TH-S/TH-S}\cxsgdelsteno0}this Brat Spot feature -- {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:4:51:0}{\*\cxs KO/KO}\cxsgdelsteno0}combined with the structural closure we mapped on the formation top.\line

\pard\s9 {\cxsgdelsteno1 {\*\cxt 10:5:2:0}{\*\cxs PA-R/PA-R}\cxsgdelsteno0}(Whereupon, the proceedings were adjourned at 10:05 a.m.)\line

}
